adjectives.description: subterrene (comparative more subterrene, superlative most subterrene)

entries.meaning: (rare) A machine for drilling or tunnelling underground.
examples: With a deafening screech of metal upon rock—which surely must echo through all the recesses of the Mountain, and waken all its nightmare brood!—the subterrene smashed through the wall and came to rest beside them.
